Always use /docs/metrics_specification.md as the source of truth for all metric calculations.  Always use /docs/portfolio_construction_policy.md as the source of truth for portfolio construction, block roles, risk budgeting, feasibility checks, liquidity logic, optimization constraints, and stress testing.  Do not invent alternative portfolio construction rules if the policy file already defines them.  If a task conflicts with the policy, explicitly flag the conflict instead of silently overriding the rules.  Before coding, first restate which rules from the specification and portfolio policy apply to the current task.
